  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "F&B Supervisor/Manager",
  "description": "<p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Vibe:</strong> You are the curator of our guest experience. You’ll ensure every detail.</p></li><li><p><strong>Service:</strong> Command the flow with confidence. Manage seating, pacing, and daily shift execution to ensure smooth, efficient operations.</p></li><li><p><strong>Develop Crew:</strong> Mentor and uplift our front-of-house team. Foster growth, encourage collaboration, and celebrate daily wins together.</p></li><li><p><strong>Excellence:</strong> Partner with management to maintain our high standards. You’ll provide thoughtful feedback and help us elevate our service every day.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>You have 1–3 years of experience in a front-of-house restaurant or café.</p></li><li><p>Formal leadership is a plus, but a natural talent for guiding and inspiring others is essential.</p></li><li><p><strong>Leader:</strong> Pressure doesn’t fluster you. You thrive when it’s busy and lead with steady, positive energy.</p></li><li><p><strong>Communicator:</strong> You guide, motivate, and unite people with respect and clarity.</p></li><li><p><strong>Partner:</strong> You are flexible and available for rotating shifts, including weekends and public holidays.</p></li></ul></p><h3><br /><br /></h3><p>EA Personnel R22110043 Tan Eng Kang</p><p>EA License 21C0430 A Dreamworks Company Pte Ltd</p>",
